# Project-local config template for the Phoenix-RTOS RPi4 dev host.
#
# Copy this to .env.local (which is gitignored) and edit for your machine:
#
#   cp .env.example .env.local
#
# .env.local is sourced by the netboot + test-cycle helper scripts
# (scripts/netboot-server-up.sh, scripts/test-cycle-netboot.sh,
# scripts/pi_reboot.sh, ...). Every value here has a safe built-in default
# in the scripts, so an unset var never hard-fails the portable build path
# ("build & flash"); these settings only matter for the optional lab rig
# (netboot / UART capture / HDMI grab / smart-plug power).
#
# The commented values below are the AUTHOR'S LAB defaults, shown as
# examples. A new user overrides only the handful they actually have.


# --- Netboot NIC (Tier-2 lab: PXE/TFTP boot the Pi over Ethernet) ---------
#
# Name of the host network interface wired directly to the Pi 4's Ethernet
# (the author uses an RTL8153 USB-Ethernet adapter over a crossover cable;
# its predictable name derives from the adapter MAC). Script default: eth1.
#RPI4B_NETBOOT_IFACE=enx00e04c68013a

# Pi 4 Ethernet MAC — used by test-cycle-netboot.sh to grep dnsmasq.log for
# the DHCPACK that confirms the Pi reached the firmware netboot stage.
#RPI4B_PI_MAC=dc:a6:32:3c:dd:f1

# Where dnsmasq serves the bootfs from and keeps its lease/state.
# Both default (in scripts) to paths under the buildroot / artifacts dir.
#RPI4B_NETBOOT_TFTPROOT=/abs/path/to/.buildroot/_boot/aarch64a72-generic-rpi4b/rpi4b-bootfs
#RPI4B_NETBOOT_STATE_DIR=/abs/path/to/artifacts/netboot


# --- Serial console / UART capture (Tier-2 lab) ---------------------------
#
# USB-UART adapter device. Default: unset -> capture-rpi4b-uart.sh
# autodetects (prefers /dev/serial/by-id/*, falls back to /dev/ttyUSB*/
# ttyACM*). Set this to pin a device and skip autodetect.
#RPI4B_SERIAL_DEV=/dev/ttyUSB0


# --- HDMI capture (Tier-2 lab: grab the Pi's HDMI output) -----------------
#
# V4L2 device of the USB HDMI grabber. Script default: /dev/video4.
#RPI4B_HDMI_GRABBER=/dev/video4


# --- SD-card flashing -----------------------------------------------------
#
# Target device for scripts/write-sdimg.sh (macOS-oriented; uses diskutil).
# NO default on purpose — a wrong device can erase host disks. Pass just the
# macOS disk identifier (find it with `diskutil list`); the script derives
# both /dev/<disk> and the raw /dev/r<disk> node.
#RPI4B_SD_DEV=disk4


# --- Smart-plug power control (Tier-2 lab) --------------------------------
#
# Absolute path to a script that toggles the Pi's smart plug. Invoked as
# "<script> on" / "<script> off" by scripts/pi_power_on.sh / pi_power_off.sh.
# If unset (and the author's-lab default path is absent), the power toggle
# is SKIPPED (non-fatal) so machines without a plug still run build/test.
#MEROSS_PLUG_SCRIPT=/home/houp/meross-plug/plug.py


# --- Toolchain ------------------------------------------------------------
#
# bin/ dir of the aarch64-phoenix cross toolchain built by
# scripts/build-phoenix-toolchain-linux.sh. Default resolves under the
# repo's .toolchain/ once built.
#PHOENIX_AARCH64_TOOLCHAIN=$HOME/phoenix-rpi/.toolchain/aarch64-phoenix/bin
